 Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["(1997: 122;2010: NA)","Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Bo Young, Chae, Chong Hwan, Dong Kun, Ho, Hwan, Hyun, Jong, Jung, Ki Soon, Kwang.  Korean Min, Chong, Chol, Jung Ho, Myong, Sa, Sung Kyun.","Korean (오; Chinese character: 吳): historically, there were two Chinese characters for the O surname, but by the late Koryŏ period (14th century  AD ), one of them had disappeared. Some records indicate that there are as many as 210 different clans for the remaining character, but only sixteen can be positively documented. All sixteen of these clans originate from the same ancestor, O Ch’ŏm (吳 瞻), who migrated to Korea from China during the reign of Shilla's King Chijŭng (500–514  AD ). <i>O</i> is a common surname throughout Korea. Compare   Oh  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Oh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Sung, Jung, Yong, Chang, Kwang, Sang, Dong, Hyun, Jae, Jin, Kyung, Jong, Chong, Chung, Byung, Jeong, Pyong, Myong, Hak, Jin Hwan, Sook, Yeong, Choon.","Korean: variant of   O  .","Japanese: variant of <b>Ō</b> (see   O  )."]}]},{"name":"Gilla","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Priscilla  , associated chiefly with the Liverpudlian singer and TV personality  Cilla Black  (  b. 1943 ), whose real name is  Priscilla White ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Michil","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical.  See  <b>Michael</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Michael","meanings":["form of a common biblical name (meaning ‘who is like God?’ in Hebrew) borne by one of the archangels, the protector of the ancient Hebrews, who is also regarded as a saint of the Catholic Church. In the Middle Ages, Michael was regarded as captain of the heavenly host (see Revelation 12:7–9), symbol of the Church Militant, and patron of soldiers. He was often depicted bearing a flaming sword. The name is also borne by a Persian prince and ally of Belshazzar mentioned in the Book of Daniel. Since the early 1900s it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names in the English-speaking world.  See also  Michal ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Cináed Gilla Michil Ó Braenain was born about 1042, in Leinster, Ireland as the son of Echmarcach Macbreannain O Brien. He had at least 1 daughter with Iuchdelb Hui Garbita of Felmeda."},"et":{"about 1042–":"umbes 1042–Surnud","1042–Male":"1042–Surnud","1070–1090":"1070–1090","1045–Female":"1045–Surnud","1062–1140":"1062–1140","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1009–Male":"1009–Surnud","1090":"1090","about 1062":"umbes 1062","about 1070":"umbes 1070","1045":"1045","1042":"1042","1140":"1140","1062":"1062","about 1042":"umbes 1042","1070":"1070","1009":"1009","Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Leinster, Ireland":"Leinster, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1042–":"noin 1042–Kuollut","1042–Male":"1042–Kuollut","1070–1090":"1070–1090","1045–Female":"1045–Kuollut","1062–1140":"1062–1140","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1009–Male":"1009–Kuollut","1090":"1090","about 1062":"noin 1062","about 1070":"noin 1070","1045":"1045","1042":"1042","1140":"1140","1062":"1062","about 1042":"noin 1042","1070":"1070","1009":"1009","Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti","Leinster, Ireland":"Leinster, Irlanti"},"fr":{"about 1042–":"environ 1042–Décédé","1042–Male":"1042–Décédé","1070–1090":"1070–1090","1045–Female":"1045–Décédée","1062–1140":"1062–1140","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée","1009–Male":"1009–Décédé","1090":"1090","about 1062":"environ 1062","about 1070":"environ 1070","1045":"1045","1042":"1042","1140":"1140","1062":"1062","about 1042":"environ 1042","1070":"1070","1009":"1009","Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, Irlande","Ireland":"Irlande","Leinster, Ireland":"Leinster, Irlande","lifeSummary":"Cináed Gilla Michil Ó Braenain est né environ 1042, à Leinster, Irlande, fils 